  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0ba4\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b8e\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bb2\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b86\u0ba4\u0bb0\u0bb5\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bb4\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0baf\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0b87\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc1 -  \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bc7\u0bb7\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc1\u0ba3\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0ba9",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "It is impossible to hide the fact that many opposition parties supported Ranil in the presidential election - Dinesh Gunawardena",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "Chief Minister Dinesh Gunawardena told the House that it cannot be hidden that most members of the opposition have voted in support of Ranil Wickremesinghe who contested as a candidate during the secret ballot for the presidential election.",
        "He mentioned the above in his address following the announcement of the results of the presidential poll held today (20) Wednesday in Parliament.",
        "It is the second time in Sri Lankan political history that the President has been elected through Parliament.",
        "President Ranil Wickremesinghe, who has won with majority support, can fulfill his responsibilities as he is the longest serving member of Parliament and has served as Prime Minister and Minister.",
        "The country is facing an unprecedented challenge due to the corona virus. After several months, the challenge was overcome.",
        "However, like other countries in the world, Sri Lanka faced an economic crisis due to the protests, which forced former President Gotabaya Rajapaksa to resign from the presidency.",
        "It is true that many members of the opposition voted for us in the secret ballot to elect the President.",
        "There is nothing to hide in that. I also thank the presidential candidates Anurakumara Dissanayake and Dalus Alagapperuma.",
        "Political position may change. But man is one for all. The world has proven that things don't always happen the same way. He said that we can overcome the challenge that the country is facing."
      ],
